content:
You can use change sets to move bots between sandbox and production. Testing your bot in a sandbox and then moving it to production ensures your bot works as designed and reduces downtime.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To build and manage Einstein Bots: 
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

Before creating a change set, make sure your source and destination orgs have a deployment connection.

In your source org, create an outbound change set.
Select the Bot component type, and then select your bot name. Click Add to Change Set.
Click View/Add Dependencies. Select the bot version you want to include, and then select Add to Change Set.
If your bot references custom flow definitions or Apex classes, include those components.
Upload your outbound change set.

When the change set is available in your target org, deploy your change set. Your bot is available on the Einstein Bots setup page.

Troubleshooting:
Make sure to include the bot version where you’re making changes in the change set.
If you’ve deleted a dialog that was attached to an intent set, you may have a stuck intent set.

To migrate a bot with changes in multiple languages, select the Language Translation component type and include the secondary language.
title: Migrating Einstein Bots Between Orgs
